        "media_position_mobile": "bottom",
        "media_width": "7",
        "content_position": "middleLeft",
        "subheading": "<p>The pieces we return to, every day.</p>",
        "title": "<p>Worn Before, Worn Again</p>",
        "description": "<p>Some pieces are chosen to mark a moment. An engagement. A wedding day. A milestone that feels impossible to forget.</p><p>But perhaps their greatest purpose isn't to commemorate a single chapter. It's to remain. To quietly accompany us through the ordinary moments that follow, collecting new memories with every wear.</p><p>Over time, jewellery begins to hold a different kind of meaning. It becomes part of our everyday uniform, woven into morning rituals, celebrations, quiet afternoons, and all the moments in between. No longer simply a reminder of where we've been, but a companion to where we're going.</p><p>For this chapter of <strong>Worn Before, Worn Again</strong>, we asked <strong>Shona</strong> to reflect on how her relationship with her Natalie Marie Jewellery pieces has evolved over time, and what it means to wear them today.</p>",
        "colour_style": "dark",
        "button_1_text": "",
        "button_1_link": "",
        "button_style": "underline"
      }
    },
